    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-03-02T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-03-02T06:00:00-05:00" n="786"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d786">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">702.5181/20: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hayes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-03-02T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >March 2, 1943—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 6:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>480. I raised this matter with the Foreign Minister on February 22 along the
                    lines of the <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> transmitted with my despatch
                    number 573 of January 15.<note n="31" xml:id="d786fn31">Neither printed; see
                        telegram No. 101, January 14, midnight, <ref target="#pg_733">p.
                        733</ref>.</note> Jordana said that after all Spain does <pb facs="0748"
                        n="736" xml:id="pg_736"/> recognize the Vichy Government which had the right
                    to get rid of Consuls disloyal to it. Without withdrawing from the position
                    taken in my <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi>, I pointed out that this was a
                    practical matter and expressed the hope that the Government would discourage the
                    supplanting of the present French Consuls and any disturbance to the <hi
                        rend="italic">status quo</hi>. Jordana said he would give consideration to
                    my views but gave no assurances.</p>
                <p>Your 456, February 27, midnight.<note n="32" xml:id="d786fn32">See footnote 29,
                            <ref target="#pg_735">p. 735</ref>.</note> Repeated to Tangier and
                    Algiers for R. Murphy.<note n="33" xml:id="d786fn33">Robert D. Murphy, Special
                        Representative of the President in French North Africa and U.S. Political
                        Adviser on the Staff of the Supreme Commander, Allied Expeditionary Force in
                        North Africa.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hayes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
